Railway Suppliers Extend Declines as India to Miss Wagon Target

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i
-- 
2011-02-28T04:54:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/railway-suppliers-extend-declines-as-india-to-miss-wagon-target.html
  India  railway suppliers extended
declines in Mumbai trading after the government said it would
buy 8 percent fewer wagons this year than planned.    Titagarh Wagons Ltd . sank 5 percent to 316 rupees as of
10:21 a.m. in Mumbai, sliding for a fifth day and set for its
lowest close since June. The stock fell 13 percent on Feb. 25.
Kalindee Rail Nirman (Engineers) Ltd. lost 5 percent to 110.5
rupees, on course for its lowest close since May 2009 after
dropping 14 percent on Feb. 25.  Indiaâ€™s state-controlled railway operator expects to
purchase 16,500 wagons by the end of next month, the end of its
financial year, compared with a target of 18,000, Vivek Sahai,
chairman of the Railway Board, the main policy body at the
Ministry of Railways, said in  New Delhi  on Feb. 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
